639: "I've run across a `}' that doesn't seem to match anything."
640: "For example, `\def\a#1{...}' and `\a}' would produce"
641: "this error. If you simply proceed now, the `\par' that"
642: "I've just inserted will cause me to report a runaway"
643: "argument that might be the root of the problem. But if"
644: "your `}' was spurious, just type `2' and it will go away."
645: "Paragraph ended before "
646: " was complete"
647: "I suspect you've forgotten a `}', causing me to apply this"
648: "control sequence to too much text. How can we recover?"
649: "My plan is to forget the whole thing and hope for the best."
650: "Use of "
651: " doesn't match its definition"
652: "If you say, e.g., `\def\a1{...}', then you must always"
653: "put `1' after `\a', since control sequence names are"
654: "made up of letters only. The macro here has not been"
655: "followed by the required stuff, so I'm ignoring it."
656: "<-"
